<doc id="79903" wikidata="Q12879099" url="?curid=79903" title="Cleta">
<text>In Greek mythology, Cleta (; means &#x27;the glorious&#x27;) was one of the Charites (Graces).

The Lakedaemonians say that the Charites are the two who gave them the names of Cleta and Phaenna. Her name means &quot;renowned&quot;.

