<doc id="79931" wikidata="Q2883647" url="?curid=79931" title="Baptes">
<text>The Baptes () were priests of the Greek goddess Kotys. The word comes from the Greek verb &quot;βάπτω&quot; (&quot;baptō&quot;), meaning &quot;to dip in water&quot;. The Baptes practised nocturnal ceremonies, which were associated with rampant obscenity and insobriety.

==See also==
*List of Greek deities

